<body>

<p>In pachira, transactions can also be imported through .csv files.
This is quite convenient for handle certain repetitive transactions.</p>

<p>First create a csv file with following column headings on the first row:</p>

<ul>
<li>Account Name</li>
<li>Date</li>
<li>Action</li>
<li>Category</li>
<li>Payee</li>
<li>Security Name</li>
<li>Amount</li>
<li>Quantity</li>
</ul>

<p>The remaining file would contain transactions to be imported.
Any line with empty Account Name or empty Date would be skipped.
Currently, only the following Action types are supported:</p>

<table>
    <tr><th align="left">Action</th><th align="left">Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>BUY   </td><td>Buy shares </td></tr>
    <tr><td>SELL  </td><td>Sale shares</td></tr>
    <tr><td>DIV</td><td>Cash dividend</td></tr>
    <tr><td>REINVDIV</td><td>Reinvest dividend</td></tr>
    <tr><td>INTINC</td><td>Interest income</td></tr>
    <tr><td>REINVINT</td><td>Reinvest interest</td></tr>
    <tr><td>CGLONG</td><td>Long-term capital gain</td></tr>
    <tr><td>CGMID</td><td>Mid-term capital gain</td></tr>
    <tr><td>CGSHORT</td><td>Short-term capital gain</td></tr>
    <tr><td>REINVLG</td><td>Reinvest long-term capital gain</td></tr>
    <tr><td>REINVMD</td><td>Reinvest mid-term capital gain</td></tr>
    <tr><td>REINVSH</td><td>Reinvest short-term capital gain</td></tr>
    <tr><td>DEPOSIT</td><td>Deposit into the account</td></tr>
    <tr><td>WITHDRAW</td><td>Withdraw from the account</td></tr>
</table>

<p>Once the csv file is ready, in Pachira, select 
File -> Import... -> Transactions - CSV
to import the transactions.</p>

